Interface Transformable

All Known Implementing Classes:
CliquesContractor, GraphConnector, SimpleGraph, Smoothing, StatsTransformer, StubsFilter
public interface Transformable

This interface allows the transformation of an input graph (which occurs inplace), for instance an edge contraction.

Method Detail

transform

public int transform(Graph pGraph)
Transforms the input graph (e.g. by adding/removing edges) inplace, i.e. no copy of the graph will be made.

Parameters:
pGraph - Graph that will be transformed.
Returns:
Number of transformations made to the graph, in particular 0 is returned if no changes to the graph were made.
